<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Go Subcommand</title><link>https://arran4.github.io/go-subcommand/</link><description>Recent content on Go Subcommand</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><atom:link href="https://arran4.github.io/go-subcommand/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>CLI Reference</title><link>https://arran4.github.io/go-subcommand/docs/reference/cli-reference/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://arran4.github.io/go-subcommand/docs/reference/cli-reference/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="cli-reference"&gt;CLI Reference&lt;a class="anchor" href="#cli-reference"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;gosubc&lt;/code&gt; tool has the following commands:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="generate"&gt;&lt;code&gt;generate&lt;/code&gt;&lt;a class="anchor" href="#generate"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Generates the Go code for your CLI.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;gosubc generate &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;flags&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Flags:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;--dir &amp;lt;path&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt;: The project root directory containing &lt;code&gt;go.mod&lt;/code&gt;. Defaults to &lt;code&gt;.&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;--man-dir &amp;lt;path&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt;: Directory to generate Unix man pages in. If omitted, no man pages are generated.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="list"&gt;&lt;code&gt;list&lt;/code&gt;&lt;a class="anchor" href="#list"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lists all identified subcommands in the project. Useful for debugging parsing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;gosubc list &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;flags&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Flags:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;--dir &amp;lt;path&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt;: The project root directory.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="validate"&gt;&lt;code&gt;validate&lt;/code&gt;&lt;a class="anchor" href="#validate"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Validates subcommand definitions for conflicts or errors.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Getting Started</title><link>https://arran4.github.io/go-subcommand/docs/usage/getting-started/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://arran4.github.io/go-subcommand/docs/usage/getting-started/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="getting-started"&gt;Getting Started&lt;a class="anchor" href="#getting-started"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Let&amp;rsquo;s build a simple CLI application named &lt;code&gt;greet&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="1-create-a-go-module"&gt;1. Create a Go Module&lt;a class="anchor" href="#1-create-a-go-module"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;mkdir greet
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;cd greet
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;go mod init example.com/greet&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="2-define-a-command"&gt;2. Define a Command&lt;a class="anchor" href="#2-define-a-command"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Create &lt;code&gt;main.go&lt;/code&gt; and define your command function.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-go" data-lang="go"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;package&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;main&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;fmt&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Hello is a subcommand `greet hello`&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Prints a greeting.&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;func&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Hello&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;name&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;string&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;fmt&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Printf&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Hello, %s!\n&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;name&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;func&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;main&lt;/span&gt;() {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// This will be replaced by the generated code usage,&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// but for now you can leave it empty or use it to run the generated cmd.&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="3-configure-generation"&gt;3. Configure Generation&lt;a class="anchor" href="#3-configure-generation"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Create a &lt;code&gt;generate.go&lt;/code&gt; file to instruct &lt;code&gt;go generate&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Defining Commands</title><link>https://arran4.github.io/go-subcommand/docs/usage/defining-commands/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://arran4.github.io/go-subcommand/docs/usage/defining-commands/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="defining-commands"&gt;Defining Commands&lt;a class="anchor" href="#defining-commands"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Commands are defined by adding specific comments to your Go functions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="syntax"&gt;Syntax&lt;a class="anchor" href="#syntax"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-go" data-lang="go"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// FunctionName is a subcommand `root-cmd sub-cmd...`&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Description text...&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;FunctionName&lt;/strong&gt;: The name of the Go function to execute.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;root-cmd&lt;/strong&gt;: The name of your root application (e.g., &lt;code&gt;git&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;kubectl&lt;/code&gt;).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;sub-cmd&amp;hellip;&lt;/strong&gt;: A space-separated list of subcommands (e.g., &lt;code&gt;remote add&lt;/code&gt;).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;a class="anchor" href="#description"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The text following the command definition or on subsequent lines is used as the command description in usage text.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Installation</title><link>https://arran4.github.io/go-subcommand/docs/introduction/installation/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://arran4.github.io/go-subcommand/docs/introduction/installation/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="installation"&gt;Installation&lt;a class="anchor" href="#installation"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To use &lt;strong&gt;Go Subcommand&lt;/strong&gt;, you need to install the &lt;code&gt;gosubc&lt;/code&gt; CLI tool.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="prerequisites"&gt;Prerequisites&lt;a class="anchor" href="#prerequisites"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Go&lt;/strong&gt;: Version 1.18 or later.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="installing-gosubc"&gt;Installing &lt;code&gt;gosubc&lt;/code&gt;&lt;a class="anchor" href="#installing-gosubc"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Run the following command to install the latest version:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;go install github.com/arran4/go-subcommand/cmd/gosubc@latest&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Verify the installation:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;gosubc --help&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="adding-to-your-project"&gt;Adding to Your Project&lt;a class="anchor" href="#adding-to-your-project"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You don&amp;rsquo;t need to import &lt;code&gt;go-subcommand&lt;/code&gt; in your application logic files unless you are using specific helper types. The generated code will reside in a separate package (usually &lt;code&gt;cmd/appname&lt;/code&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Flags &amp; Parameters</title><link>https://arran4.github.io/go-subcommand/docs/usage/flags-parameters/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://arran4.github.io/go-subcommand/docs/usage/flags-parameters/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="flags--parameters"&gt;Flags &amp;amp; Parameters&lt;a class="anchor" href="#flags--parameters"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;go-subcommand&lt;/code&gt; automatically maps your function parameters to command-line flags and arguments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="automatic-mapping"&gt;Automatic Mapping&lt;a class="anchor" href="#automatic-mapping"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Function parameters are converted to flags by default.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-go" data-lang="go"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;func&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Server&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;port&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;verbose&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;bool&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Generates flags:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;--port &amp;lt;int&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;--verbose&lt;/code&gt; (boolean flag)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Flag names are automatically converted to kebab-case (e.g., &lt;code&gt;maxRetries&lt;/code&gt; -&amp;gt; &lt;code&gt;--max-retries&lt;/code&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="customizing-flags"&gt;Customizing Flags&lt;a class="anchor" href="#customizing-flags"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can customize flags using comments. There are three ways to define them, in order of priority:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Flags Block&lt;/strong&gt;: A &lt;code&gt;Flags:&lt;/code&gt; block in the function documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Inline Comment&lt;/strong&gt;: Comment on the same line as the parameter.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preceding Comment&lt;/strong&gt;: Comment on the line before the parameter.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;h3 id="1-flags-block-highest-priority"&gt;1. Flags Block (Highest Priority)&lt;a class="anchor" href="#1-flags-block-highest-priority"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-go" data-lang="go"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// MyCmd is a subcommand `app cmd`&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Flags:&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// port: default: 8080 description: Port to listen on&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;func&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;MyCmd&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;port&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;) {}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="2-inline-comment"&gt;2. Inline Comment&lt;a class="anchor" href="#2-inline-comment"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-go" data-lang="go"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;func&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;MyCmd&lt;/span&gt;(
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;port&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// default: 8080 description: Port to listen on&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;) {}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="3-preceding-comment"&gt;3. Preceding Comment&lt;a class="anchor" href="#3-preceding-comment"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-go" data-lang="go"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// default: 8080 description: Port to listen on&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;port&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="syntax-reference"&gt;Syntax Reference&lt;a class="anchor" href="#syntax-reference"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The parameter definition syntax supports several attributes:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>